    "body": "After some testing I think the problem was not solved, adding `*` to filters will still have the problem:\n\n``` js\nrequire('remote').require('dialog').showSaveDialog({\n  defaultPath: 'C:\\\\test',\n  filters: [\n    { name: 'All Files', extensions: ['*'] }\n  ]\n})\n```\n\n<img width=\"604\" alt=\"screen shot 2015-10-27 at 2 50 44 pm\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/639601/10751323/47ea38c2-7cba-11e5-9407-7dbc0c95b44f.png\">\n\nAnd this change also makes the the default save dialog show empty in \"Save as type\":\n\n<img width=\"600\" alt=\"screen shot 2015-10-27 at 2 47 23 pm\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/639601/10751329/622e6dc0-7cba-11e5-969f-7238d0050a6c.png\">\n\nIt seems that the problem is in how we add the extension to filename, no in the default \"All files\" filter.\n"
